Fans of fish are sure to love this nutritious yet delicious Asian-inspired recipe. Even better, the whole thing comes together in less than 30 minutes. That just means you've got more time to enjoy the appealing umami flavour of this tangy teriyaki dish.

== Garlic Rice ==

Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Rinse the @rice{150%grams} to remove excess starch. Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with @butter{1%tbsp}.

Once hot, fry the garlic for ~{1%minute} then add rice, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{300%ml}.

Bring to the boil then lower heat to medium, cover and cook for ~{10%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Salmon ==

Meanwhile, lay the @salmon{200%grams}, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Once the oven is hot, roast the salmon on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish. Salmon is cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Broccoli ==

Meanwhile, trim the tip of the @broccoli{1}. Cut head into florets and stem into 2cm pieces.

Place a #pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the broccoli for ~{2-3%minutes} then add a splash of @water{to taste} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until the broccoli is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer to a #bowl{} and stir through half the @sesame oil{20%ml}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, cover to keep warm and set aside.

== Teriyaki Sauce ==

Return the pan to medium heat.

Pour the @teriyaki sauce{1%sachet}, @water{25%ml}, half the @sesame seeds{10%grams} and remaining sesame oil into the pan.

Stir together and cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Loosen the sauce with another splash of water if you feel it's too thick.

== Assembly ==

Once the fish is cooked, carefully add it to the pan (reheat the sauce first if needed).

Turn the salmon to coat in the glaze.

When everything is ready, fluff up the garlic rice with a #fork{} and divide between plates.

Top with the teriyaki salmon, spooning over any sauce left in the pan.

Sprinkle over the remaining sesame seeds.

Serve the broccoli alongside.